reviews_data.review_text: Lovely study spot with great coffee and espresso!!

This place is seriously beautiful -- I love the aesthetic and the natural, organic design. It feels super cozy, and there are lots of spots to sit, whether you're meeting up with a friend or trying to get some work done.

That said, the food takes forever. I waited 15 minutes for just one empanada, and it wasn't even that busy. It's not the first time either, so just keep that in mind if you're in a hurry.

Also, the WiFi hasn't worked either time I've been here, which is a bummer if you're hoping to get stuff done.

Great vibes overall, but definitely not the place if you're short on time or need reliable internet.

Got my drink size completely wrong. Didn't if I wanted cream, it's 2025 put the cream out were we can use it ourselves. Microwaved my pastry without asking. They give you a discount for using cash but don't have change available. Complete rip off for the quality of service and product offered. If you think this place is great you've never experienced a true coffee shop.

I was really excited to have a breakfast at this place but the experience is super disappointing! The lady who took our order hardly speaks English, I asked for a sandwich and fully cooked egg inside because I'm pregnant (btw their croissant is not real croissant it's just a bread) and my husband asked for the same, in the end they charged for 2 sandwiches but made just one (we forgot to take the check) so ended up paying extra 10$ for another one. I would say this place is just a hype, yes nice decor and atmosphere overall but the customer service should be better!
Truly one of the best cup of coffees I've had in clt

First time trying the place, and will try again in the future. 1st wanted to point out the cashier was super nice and friendly and welcoming on my trip, also i love the ambiance of the place and the light the windows provide. That being said i came here to try this place specifically for the outside patio, which i was very dissapointed in and may be the foundation of this review. The outside area is on the perfect side of the building and has amazinf outdoor furniture and space, that being said none of the egg chairs or patio chairs had cushions making them super uncomfortable to sit in. We found a nice table and chairs out there anyways and went to put up the umbrellas as they were down and we planned to do laptop work and needed a bit of shade on the screens. Let me note that there was no note, no signage, no indication of anything wrong here, i just had simply thought someone had put them down to enjoy the sunlight( i sure was) but much to my suprise the umbrella was super broken, and a string was hanging. No big deal really it was dissapointing but not the end of the world. What made it bad was the man that slowly came out of the building to barrade us about trying to put it up and being rude , we simply stated we didnt know it was broken , he didnt say anything further, but actually walked to another table that was out to tie a rope around it and the really sweet ladies also asked him if their umbrella was out of order, he stated " yes and no matter how many times we tie them up customers take them down" she mentioned maybe putting a sign up. to which he stated, that if they would just not touch it there would be no problem, the ladies were appalled and actually left, we moved inside after the interaction of the rude employee. The man had long hair about shoulder length, a 5 oclock shadow, and a mustach that connected to chin hair, he was wearing a beige hat and button up. Looked to be early 30s late 20s. Managment should really have a talk with him. If he hates the public and his job this much this is not the environment for him. The good in the review was the raspberry sweet tea and the amount of plugs. I would also like to mention maybe getting some back rest cusions on the benches. i did enjoy the sliding butt cushions though. Would give another try but if i walked into this employee again i would leave again. He was very offputting and seemed hostile.

We didn't expect to have such an amazing lunch here but we did! The matcha is great, the empanadas are delicious, and the sandwiches were excellent. Lots of gluten free options as well. Such an amazing meal!

It is great coffee shop. Very spacious place. I liked empanadas and power bowl with quinoa for breakfast.
Staff is very nice and polite.

Great place for a coffee meeting or bite to eat! The interior has a ton of space for a business meeting or professional coffee date, and the food and drinks are awesome. Get the Sumaq Latte, you'll be glad you did!
Always great service by the staff. Great food and drinks.

Coffee Shop No.472
SUMAQ - Coffee Bakery Music
Charlotte, NC
March 9, 2025

My family and I were off to a late start. SUMAQ was out of the way. I told my husband to just get on the interstate we have a long way to drive. Thankfully he said, "Let's just go."

SUMAQ was extremely busy on a Sunday morning. The three folks working the register and coffee station were absolute pros. They have a very efficient system; so if you walk in, see a long line, and think about leaving. DO NOT. The line moved quickly and we received our coffee quickly. The food took a bit longer, but it was absolutely worth it. The atmosphere was warm, bright, and inviting. This is definitely a great spot to meet family or friends to chat and eat good food.

When I order a cortado the first thing I notice is the size of the cup it comes in. A cortado is a 1:1 ratio of espresso and steam milk; so when I was handed a petite coffee mug excitement and anticipation rose up in me. I quickly took a few photos then a sip of the cortado. The texture was not as velvety as I would have liked, but the flavor of the espresso was excellent. I immediately grabbed my husband's dirty chai to taste it. Delicious. Whatever coffee bean SUMAQ is using and the method they are using to brew is magical.

SUMAQ was absolutely worth detour!

Enjoying life one cortado at a time.

I was traveling in the area and looking for a solid latte. Sumaq came up on Google and it did not disappoint. I had an iced white mocha strawberry latte and it was delicious. Smooth with the perfect amount of sweetness. The server also recommended the beef empanadas. While I don't tend to gravitate to an empanada, it was truly phenomenal. Crunchy on the outside and warm and soft on the inside. I'll definitely come back if I'm in the area.

This a very cute establishment, coffee was great, empanadas were fine. However the service was not the best the cashier was not friendly at all. My order was wrong and when i approached the gentleman handling the food, he seemed inconvenienced by it.
Great coffee, friendly atmosphere.
El cafe estaba bien rico, y la torta de chocolate super recomendada.
Cute cafe in south charlotte. The staff was friendly and the ambiance is ideal for working, and studying
Great coffee menu, nice selection of eats, friendly service.  A nice selection of large and small tables.
Great spot with great coffee!
Really good latte
great spot! I am surprised that I haven't come sooner but would love to go to one of their events or spend an afternoon here reading - also it's so nice to have a coffee shop that's open late
Nothing special. Coffee was alright, tasted like I could have gotten at Starbucks. Food took over 20 minutes to come out for one piece of toast. Ridiculously over priced.

Sumaq keeps me coming back for their absolutely delicious strawberry matcha. Their coffee drinks, pastries, and food are all great as well. Very happy to have found this place and highly recommend it. Not to mention, the atmosphere is very inviting.

I thrive in coffee shops! Visiting @sumaqclt was the highlight of my day! The space is so open yet still felt connected. The history, values and Peruvian culture is super apparent and warming.
I could've sat in there all day and felt right at home!

My friend brought me to Sumaq for my birthday. As this was Saturday, the place was packed! The line circled nearly around the place. But they were knocking orders out like pros!

We were lucky to find two spots to sit.
Everything was tasty! The coffee was perfect!

Enjoy 

Josephine Local Guide
Gluten free waffles with Nutella are good enough for my non gf family members. The turmeric latte and the cappuccinos were on point too. Not too sweet.
Very great to hangout with friendsII i
Good vibes. Baked food was not good
Breakfast options are delicious
As always was very good, the coffee and their food menu are very good, you have to try their flat breads and they Colombian pastries like empanadas and the guava paste roll.
Strong coffee . Excellent spot for a coffee!
The staff didn't greet us and the lady taking my order was very dry. Never coming back to this place. The prices are ridiculous, there's a hidden surcharge for everything.
walking in here felt like a little oasis. I loved the atmosphere. I liked the deserts a lot and the coffees were great.
Very noisy atmosphere. The croissant didn't come with butter or cream cheese.

I was SO excited to try this place with my boyfriend. We're always very careful eating out because he has severe peanut/tree nut allergies. There was a slight language barrier with the woman taking our order, when asking to make sure there isn't any cross contamination with the foods. Most places accommodate his allergies by leaving a note with the chef, but she refused to ask. She immediately said no. After I asked to speak to the chef, he came out and dryly said everything is prepared on the same surface followed by a careless shrug. It was disappointing that wiping down a counter top and just taking extra precaution for a customer was too much. If that'd be too much we'd completely understand but the lack of warmth and the low tolerance for a short discussion with eager customers was frustrating.
Despite how much I wanted to try this place I felt that I'd rather spend my money in a place that's more polite and communicative with their customers. Hoping they can improve customer service moving forward.
I got a latte, pastry, & breakfast sandwich, so good! Will definitely be coming back soon!
Fantastic atmosphere with lively energy. Don't miss the Wallpa Quad sandwich--it's a must-try! It can get crowded on weekends, but the food is absolutely worth it.
Enjoyed the Sumaq Latte! Nice vibe. Stopped here on my trip in Charlotte.
Relaxing with good coffee
Was crowded as hell, had to wait 5 minutes for a table. Do not recommend it during lunch hours. Other than that desserts are delicious
Best coffee experience in a year!

The place is so cute! i love the aesthetic, super clean and plenty of open indoor seating.
We ordered the Wallpa Quad, Guava and Cheese bread, Wasi House, and the Coconut Guava drink.
The Wallpa Quad was good but the chicken was dry, and the Wasi House sandwich was delicious, but again the chicken was also dry.
I do not recommend the guava and cheese bread, it was super dry and little filling. Coffee was great! Absolutely loved this setting!
Great chill place. Staff was very kind and helpful.  Other than the little turd girl ordering in front of my thinking the world revolved around her, it was fantastic .
Love this place

The atmosphere is really pretty but unfortunately the coffee is not too well. My iced vanilla latte was extremely watery and the cold foam was very thin. It was obvious that store bought syrup is being used. The waffles they have though, are amazing and worth coming back for. I love the fact that there's cheese inside but you can barely taste it. Gives it that sweet and salty combo.

We love that we have a local coffee shop here. As we come often, but we feel now it's losing its appeal. Today, as we ordered our coffee, she was on her cell phone. And paying $15 for coffee we feel the staff shouldn't be on their cell. She seems like she is new.
Not sure if will keep coming back now. Sucks, seems Charlotte has this issue.

Wonderful place, great food and atmosphere BUT, if the owner doesn't keep a close eye on things and learns to get the food out the out quicker they're going to run into problems. As an ex successful restaurant owner, I know these things..
It was okay, I was expecting it to be busy on a Saturday but wow. Waiting 15 minutes for a coffee is alot when they have 3 baristas working. I found it to be over priced and not great.

This place was recommended by so many locals during our vacation and it lived up to the hype. It easily made my top 3 favorite coffee shops. They have mouth watering desserts and parties. Their food was also so delicious. We got their chocolate dulce de leche cake and it was super delicious and almost like a mix of a cake tree leches cake. Their empanadas were super delicious as well and the ham and cheese bread was amazing.

Their Sumaq latte was amazing but what stole the show was the dulce de leche latte, that has to be one of my favorite lattes I've ever had. Not overly sweet but you can really taste that dulce de leche taste. An absolute gem and would rate it a 10/10 spot.
Empanadas are amazing
My latte tasted a little burned and my sandwich was underwhelming. Willing to try the place out again and order something different next time. The vibes are 10/10
Store bought syrup

The coffee was watered down..needed more flavor for spending $21 on 2 cups. Another issue I have is the parking lot is not the best..especially when you have douche bags parking their luxurious cars in an awkward position, making it hard for the other folks to back out of near an already busy street. The place is very nice though, clean bathrooms & nice staff. Hopefully they work on their flavors with the coffee, but definitely a must stop for a quick pick me up!

Came here for the first time today. Very happy they allowed our pet dog to come inside while we enjoyed our coffee. Ordered one iced and one hot latte and both were good. However the pastries were not. Nutella bread was burnt/hard - could not eat. Cinnamon apple bread was just ok - did not finish. Would recommend for coffee and pet friendly atmosphere but not the pastries.

Came to sumaq today and the place has a nice aesthetic and chill vibe however I would not come here again for the coffee NOR food. The frappes are not blending thoroughly, and have a lot of ice chunks, the Nutella bread that was given to me was BURNT TO A CRISP, and the empanada my friend ordered was given to her with the salsa cup dumped all over it and was soggy. There are WAY BETTER PLACES, in Charlotte.

I love this place and totally recommend it!

That's my safe island in the morning after work. I mean try to find good place with good food, nice atmosphere and reasonable prices before 11 am especially on Sunday, good luck.

That's why I love it, I can come here after work at 7,  8, 9, 10 and have that tasty coffee, nice breakfast and chill for 30 minutes to organize my thoughts and get ready for next job.

Big thanks to the owners and everyone who works there! I appreciate your hard work a lot and recommend to all my friends, and everyone liked it as much as I did!

Shukran  ( I hope I wrote it right)

This place is a unique spot in Charlotte. I came for a simple Americano coffee and ended up experiencing a joyful and warm scene of family and friends gathering and enjoying themself. I'm coming back to try those desserts and sandwiches.
Honestly they could install more outlets :D
Originally came in for a cappuccino and was pleasantly surprised at how good the food was. Breakfast flatbread was a good and the cinnamon apple pastry was great. The staff were also quite friendly.

If I lived here, I would create a separate budget for coffee everyday . Very welcoming coffee shop. The staff is super kind and helpful . I've been longing for a place that serves coffee where you can taste the coffee bean. This coffee shop is the one .
Great open environment for a new find. Good coffee, good food, smiles all around!
Super limpio exelente atencion y delicioso pan y lates
Lindo lugar, me encanta el matcha y el flatbread. Pronto probare los postres que me han recomendado mucho.

Espresso is very pleasant and balanced, although I do prefer more acidity and fruitiness in taste - it's great for daily consumption.

The biggest surprise turned out to be the dulce de lecce roll which I thought is a muffin at first - it tastes sweet enough like an European pastry, which is a big compliment since most of the time American desserts are over sweetened.

I finally got here after months of reading about this place. They have one of the cutest outdoor seating areas in Charlotte. The atmosphere was chill. The latte I got was good but the flan with the fresh blackberry in it was amazing. The prices are the same as the other coffee shops in the area overpriced at $8.00. I must be inflation because every coffee shop I have been to in the country it is same. But it was still delicious. Coming here was a very relaxing experience.
Very Chill and lovely vibe! They have the best coffee and food for anything! Everyone is super friendly and welcoming! I love chilling out here with friends or alone to work! Highly recommended
I love the atmosphere and friendly staff... Have Nutella desserts makes it a must!
beautiful interior and delicious food and coffee. not overly sweet but great flavor, empanada and egg salad was great too.

This place is beyond amazing!!! The coffee was not only delicious but had an amazing presentation. Even though it was busy they took the time and pride to serve everything perfectly. This might be the best coffee shop I have been to in years. Keep up the good work.

I recently discovered Sumaq heading to the Charlotte airport and it was an absolute delight! The aesthetic is stunning, with cozy seating and beautiful decor that creates the perfect atmosphere for relaxation or catching up with friends.

The coffee was top-notch--rich and flavorful, expertly brewed to perfection. I tried their signature latte, and it was a masterpiece both in taste and presentation. The baristas were knowledgeable and passionate about their craft, offering great recommendations.
Very nice place, good menu, service and atmosphere. Thank you, team!
Delicioso cafe y tarta de limon excelente  atendido por Estefeny grata persona

I love going here when I have free time and to work! Its really nice, the food is delicious, the pantries are great and same with the drinks! The customer service is amazing and they treat you very well.
My favorite coffee shop I've found in Charlotte!

Great coffee, my favorite in Charlotte. But, TERRIBLE customer service. There is one particular guy who seems annoyed to serve you. Been there several times to buy their yuca waffles (which are great) and have been denied the order because I was too "late." They closed the kitchen 30 minutes prior to 7 and even tough I arrived 31 minutes early he will state that I was late with a terrible attitude. Unfortunately, although this was my favorite spot in Charlotte for coffee and a snack, I am never going back. I might be just one customer but I swear I was a loyal one.

A very nice coffee place with great ambiance. The coffee was also very good and it came in large mugs, just the way I like it. The pastries were fine. Not the best we've eaten but not bad either. Would go there again for coffee and the ambiance
Love this place! Just wish they were open earlier!
Absolutely loved this place! The Sumaq waffles were devine with the dolce de leche and the match was amazing!! Will be coming back!!
I stopped in this place for remote working and a liked. I recommend.
Great coffee shop to work from, good vibes, good food, good service, good coffee, good everything!
Locate right out on the main road so easy for morning commute.

I love the decor. It reminds me of the Cafes in Korea.  I had the Sumaq Latte, and my husband had a hot chocolate with a slice of carrot cake. The latte was very good, and because of the cinnamon, it made me think of the coffees in Mexico. So good! My husband really liked the carrot cake and I agree the frosting was very good. Next time I'm in the area I'll definitely be back.
Great coffee shop! And their cafe con leche is delicious!! The steak Walpa Wrap was so flavorful yet light and refreshing but still filling.
Excellent empanadas. Worst chocolate chip cookies- they're like a hockey puck. Slow service if you order lunch
It's a nice spot to drink something and take a break, this is my first time visiting, it's good. Great atmosphere and rest area! There are not too many  parking spaces.

Terrible service but great coffee shop. They cannot do DoorDash (will cancel every order) even though they say they can. Atmosphere is great though - filled with people -  and coffee is unique. Would recommend, but come skeptical of the staff!
Cozy place with amazing lattes
The chicken empanadas were delicious and the vanilla latte was good

I actually would like to give this cafe a 6 star!!
We are here for the first time. The food is more than excellent; what makes them stand out even further is their service: we ordered egg salad sandwich (vegetarian and without onion); it came with bacon and onion...HOWEVER, the chef came out immediately saying they couldn't remove the onion from egg salad and offered to tailor-make what we would like to have. Very customer-oriented!
Sure we will come back regularly!

Nestled on the bustling 6259 South Boulevard in Charlotte, NC, SUMAQ Coffee & Catering is a hidden gem that delights the senses from the moment you step through its doors. This review can't fully capture the enchanting experience, but I'll do my best to convey the magic that awaits you at this incredible venue. With an exquisite blend of artisanal coffee, delightful pastries, and exceptional service, SUMAQ stands out as a beacon of culinary artistry and warm hospitality.

Atmosphere & Design: A Contemporary Sanctuary

SUMAQ's exterior is unassuming yet modern, welcoming visitors into a space that feels both contemporary and cozy. The moment you walk in, you're greeted by a minimalist yet chic interior, with a tasteful combination of wooden furnishings, industrial accents, and soft lighting that creates a serene and inviting atmosphere. The outdoor patio is an oasis in itself, perfect for a sunny day or a tranquil evening under the stars. The design seamlessly blends comfort with style, making it an ideal spot for everything from a quiet morning coffee to a leisurely afternoon catch-up with friends.

Culinary Delights: A Feast for the Senses

The menu at SUMAQ is a curated selection of culinary delights that showcase a fusion of traditional and innovative flavors. The first thing that caught my eye was the signature iced matcha latte, beautifully layered in a mason jar. The vibrant green matcha contrasted elegantly with the creamy milk, creating a visual treat that was only surpassed by its taste. The matcha was of the highest quality, offering a rich, umami flavor balanced perfectly by the sweetness of the milk. It was a harmonious blend that was both refreshing and indulgent.

Not to be outdone, the iced coffee was equally impressive. Served in a similar mason jar, the coffee had a deep, robust flavor with subtle notes of chocolate and caramel. It was the perfect companion to the delicious pastries I tried next. The flan was a masterpiece, with a silky, smooth texture that melted in your mouth. Topped with a single, vibrant raspberry, it was not just a dessert but a work of art. The caramel sauce was just the right amount of sweet, providing a delightful contrast to the creamy custard.

The alfajor, a traditional South American delight, was another highlight. This delicate pastry, filled with luscious dulce de leche and dusted with powdered sugar, was a bite-sized piece of heaven. It offered a perfect balance of sweetness and texture, with the buttery, crumbly cookie surrounding a rich, caramel-like filling. It's a treat that evokes the warm, comforting flavors of Latin America, making you feel right at home.

Service: A Touch of Excellence

The service at SUMAQ is in a league of its own, largely thanks to the charismatic and attentive Juan Pablo. His passion for the cafe and its offerings is evident in every interaction. Juan Pablo's knowledge of the menu and his genuine enthusiasm make every visit special. He has an uncanny ability to make you feel like the most important guest in the room, offering personalized recommendations and ensuring that every aspect of your experience is perfect. It's rare to find such a combination of professionalism and warmth, and it's clear that Juan Pablo and the entire team at SUMAQ take great pride in their work.

A Perfect Conclusion

SUMAQ Coffee & Catering is more than just a cafe; it's a destination that promises an unforgettable experience. Whether you're a local looking for your new favorite spot or a visitor exploring the culinary scene of Charlotte, SUMAQ offers something truly special. The thoughtful design, exceptional food and beverages, and unparalleled service come together to create an experience that's both sophisticated and heartfelt. I left SUMAQ not only satisfied but inspired, eagerly anticipating my next visit. Thank you, Juan Pablo, and the wonderful team at SUMAQ, for crafting such a memorable experience. This is a five-star gem that deserves every bit of its acclaim!
I worked out of this coffee shop Nice atmosphere, delicious food, and friendly staff. The coffee was on point.

A+!

Perfect cortado and great flatbread.
The empanadas are 10/10
Loved the special service I received and the food was great! I especially enjoyed the Sumaq waffle

I came here for breakfast and a coffee yesterday. Coffee tasted fine. Sandwich was foul. The chicken tasted like it had gone bad. I ate 3-4 bites before deciding it wasnt worth finishing because I was worried the chicken had went bad so I tossed the rest in the trash. Was up all night throwing up. The only thing I can think my sickness is from was the foullll chicken in that sandwich. I'm the only one who got sick in my household and I'm also the only one who ate the chicken which makes me think it was not a stomach bug.
Beautiful and cool spot to get delicious coffees and quick bites to eat. A favorite stop!
My iced coffee was absolutely delicious. I highly recommend the brown sugar cinnamon mixture in a black iced coffee!
Cool place, great coffee and ambiance. Service was slow but they were pretty busy, so we understood. Will be back to try the food which looked legit
This is a great place to share with friends and family, great food, friendly and helpful staff and a beautiful space. The apple cinnamon cake and the berry danish were delicious.

Been here on Sunday afternoon and unfortunately place looked more like an office than a coffee shop. Most seats were busy by people and their technology. We had to sit on bar stools that were ridiculously uncomfortable, they definitely need cushions. Food and coffee was good. They do have seating outside but bc it's hot it's impossible to be there.

Definitely over priced. Paid $6 for a strawberry lemonade and watched the guy pour simply pink lemonade into a plastic cup. For $6 this should be freshly squeezed lemonade and strawberry. I could have just bought simply lemonade from Harris teeter for cheaper. Won't go back.
Anything made with dulce de leche here is amazing
Cute coffee shop. Lots of open space inside and outside. The tres leches was absolutely delicious, as was my strawberry matcha latte
One of my favorite coffee spots in Charlotte! Beautiful space and amazing coffee.
Love this place , best coffee in Charlotte
Great coffee and a super chill vibe
Not impressed with the empanada and the pineapple cake was dry.
I had egg salad sandwich and sumaq latte. Staff was very friendly

This place is seriously dirty.
There were flies in the display cabinet.
When I informed them they said "oh" didn't clean it and continued to offer pastries to clients
Simplemente un Sitio Maravilloso e Impecable

So grateful to finally find a place that offers coconut milk for iced matcha lattes, and gluten free items. The gluten free salad bowl, waffle, and tres leches dessert were all outstanding! Will definitely be back!
Extremely tasty cappuccino! I can compare it  with European top cafes
Really good stufff

Experience delightful outdoor seating with authentic Peruvian breakfast at this gem. A must-visit if you're in the area. Peru consistently offers the finest cuisine in South America, and this place is no exception. Sumaq means beautiful, pleasant in the Quechua language.
Nice coffee Shoop.
The sumaq latte was simply breath taking and refine. Pair it with the wasi house sandwich and breakfast goes after the charts. This is the best hidden gem spot to find.
Excelente me gusta
The order took longer than expected. Otherwise, anything else was good.

Another great coffee shop in CLT. This place is so nice. It's nice and open with lots of seating and room to work if you like to work from coffee shops. Staff was friendly and the drinks were good. We tried the Dulce de leche, iced vanilla latte and carrot cake. All were good. The parking and location aren't the best but that's ok.

Lovely place. Good lighting.  Easy to talk and have conversation
Nothing loud occurring like loud coffee grinders or other machines.  Pretty quiet. Peaceful. Nice clientele. And a very good hot cappuccino in a lovely cup and saucer.  A very nice treat for sure.
Coffee shop was beautiful, great service and the chai was so amazing!!
I loved this place
You will regret it if you are just driving by this place!

Soooo excited to support a Latinx-owned coffee shop! I work from home but this may be my new go-to place. Super friendly owners and beautiful aesthetic. Can't wait to see how it'll grow 

Me da alegria de haber encontrado este rinconcito. Trabajo desde casa, pero este puede ser mi nuevo lugar favorito. La gente es amable y un lugar hermoso.

Update: Please consider getting a different wifi router. Internet always falls!
Very very very !!!!!

The coffee is great. I've been several times for meetings, and I've not been disappointed with the coffee. The outdoor seating area is very nice. Traffic is heavy and is situated next to a busy road, so not a great place for small children.
Great coffee and a great atmosphere.
I've working remotely from this location.  The atmosphere is quiet enough to focus. The food and baked good are delicious. Definitely will go back soon.
Just love the place. Great people, great atmosphere and exquisite coffee and creative Peruvian snacks.

This coffee shop is truly a hidden gem. Loved the interior design. The employees are friendly and polite. I had a vanilla latte and an empanada. Both were delicious. Definitely will have to try their pastries and sandwiches next time!
The lack of customer service provided by both gentleman's was not it. (My 1st time and not coming back) If you want to be ignored when you speak this is your place!
The Maracuya cheesecake was wonderful!
Great place to spend Sunday morning!

I was pleasantly surprised!! I had a Wasi House sandwitch and Iced Dolce De Leche Latte with half of oatmilk & almond milk :) The sandwitch was so good. And the interior was so cool :)
_ _

(Mar 8th, 2024)
I haven't visited here for over 1 year (because I moved to a different county)
I ordered Quinoa Bowl (added chicken).
This is so good! I highly recommend it :)
Great empanadas and coffee on any good morning

Peruvian Coffee is delicious and delivers a smooth satisfying sip. I tried the Dulce Du Leche in an Iced Coffee. It was delicious. I also tried the empanads. Those were unique and meaty. My favorite was the cheese. We also had a light and fluffy waffle that was amazing.

I love this place! Great atmosphere and DELICIOUS food. Lots of great Peruvian items with great flavor. The house coffee was amazing and Peruvian style steak empanadas were to die for. Highly recommend!

Sumaqlicious!

Perfect place for a rainy day. Their dulce de leche cappuccino is a "you have to try it".       Food portions are definitely sharable. Not quite sure if I could share that chocolate cake though 
Thank you Elmer and David for your amazing service!
Que Experiencia Mas Increible Me Lleve En Este Lugar. El Cafe Uffale En El Mero Corazon, Y La Comida Exquisita RECOMENDADO TOTALMENTE
Outrageously delicious, food was flavorful and yet light. Coffee was strong and aromatic. Lovely atmosphere and customer service, will easily be back. (Wasi House Sandwich was unreal)
This place has such a cool vibe. Grab a coffee and sit on the patio on a nice day. Instant stress relief.
Great coffee and the BLT was delicious.  A good place to meet a friend for a bite

Great coffee shop. Tons of work space and free WiFi.

The price of the cinnamon apple cake is pretty high at $7.28/slice and we didn't care for the heavy spice in it so that was $7 wasted. I'd skip that next time.

The lady working was very nice and the drinks are filled to the brim giving you the most bang for your buck there.

Overall an enjoyable shop to get some afternoon work done at.

This cafe is amazing! Elevated casual coffee shop with all of your signature hispanic bites, empandas were delicious; and their sandwiches soooooooooo GOOD! I would absolutely come back and recommend it to everyone, their coffees are beautifully made & the customer service is just A+ everyone was so pleasant

February 27, 2024...my first time at Sumaq Coffee. The first time was absolute charm!
I got there at 10:15 a.m.. The first thing that I noticed was people from many different cultures.  Beautiful people! The ambience was very nice. They also have very nice outdoor seating.
They have coffee, tea, pastries, empanadas, and excellent sandwiches! Vegan friendly. The staff was wonderful! Very friendly and accommodating. Lots of smiles.  Five stars
Checked into a hotel close by and google this place up. With about an hour to spare before closing..I had the most enjoyable sandwich. Wasi House. Thank you.

Carrot cake was not very fresh. I believe it was good yesterday but not now.
Coffee was great!

Some tables are not cleaned from previous guests.
Overall okay but seems overpriced considering yesterday cake.
Great, delicious food and comfy environment. Very busy on a Sunday afternoon. Prices were pretty insane but you can get a small cup of coffee and not spend too much and chill with friends.

My wife and I love Sumaq.  We are passionate about our coffee and try different coffee shops every place we visit.  My wife is Spanish and I am Italian and we both grew up drinking good coffee.   The coffee at Sumaq is excellent.  It has a smooth taste, isn't acidic, never over roasted or burnt, they understand how temperature impacts a coffees taste and it the lattes are sweetened but not overwhelmingly sweet.  We recommend their Sumaq latte.  I was very impressed that the owner remembers us and what we drink and genuinely takes an interest.   If this says anything, we drive 40 minutes just to come to this coffee shop!  Highly recommend.   :))

This is one of my favorite coffee spots. I always get a cappuccino and it's super good, and I love getting their dulce de leche bread and empanadas. I love the airy and clean aesthetic they have here too!
Coffee and DulceDe Leche: not the best but above average.
Muy rico cafe y la comida!!!
Amazing chai and food! Love the owners, super sweet.

Definitivamente el mejor cafe en el que he estado, los duenos son extremadamente amables y simpaticos y se encargan de tus ordenes, el espacio esta decorado hermosamente con mucha madera y hojas y musica relajante, es muy calido 

Probe el te latte de curcuma con  de avena, un CACHITO (son unos de mis bakery favoritos en el mundo, son panes rellenos de mi pais que en mis tres anos aqui jamas he conseguido en ninguna pasteleria), un cheesecake de fruta de la pasion (que se siente el sabor real de la fruta y no es una fruta/sabor que puedes conseguir facilmente aqui) 

El latte estaba en su punto, el sabor de las especie era muy balanceada, cremoso, EL MEJOR te de curcuma que me he bebido; el cheesecake tenia una textura interesante entre un mousse y un cheesecake con un capa al tope de gelatina con semillas y debajo con una rica corteza; y por ultimo pero para nada menos importante, el cachito, el sabor/consistencia/sazon/textura del pan y el relleno eran ABSOLUTAMENTE perfectos, saben de la misma manera que en mi pais, fue una grata experiencia conseguir algo con tanto sabor tan autentico 

Pero esto no queda alli, tiempo despues de estar disfrutando mis platillos y leer un poco, llego mi pareja y disfrute de sus empanadas (fritas de maiz) rellenas de carne deshebrada, estaban delgadas, crujientes y la carne perfectamente sazonada y aproveche para que el probara los cachitos y yo robarle un poco ahahaha tambien ordeno una ada de blackberry (si mal no recuerdo) y hasta la limonada estaba increible 

Tienen una variedad exquisita cafe, te, finger food y postres, y un auto-refill de agua 

En serio estoy encantada con el concepto tanto del espacio como la comida y las bebidas, sinceramente se merecen lo mejor y mucho exito siempre, se siente el carino que le han puesto a este negocio 

Obviamente nos veremos pronto y mas seguido 

1 trillon % recomendado

What a great coffee shop! Love this place. My vanilla latte was excellent.  We also had a ham n cheese bread roll and it's excellent. The owner has a hit here. The shop is beautiful. Great place to meet n greet. Very highly recommended!
Great hot and iced coffee. Food here is great. Not overpriced, which is rare for a coffee shop. Empanadas were really spectacular

Recently discovered Sumaq and absolutely adore this place. Great selection of savory foods and sweet treats, stellar selection (and presentation) of coffee and matcha drinks, and a cozy, welcoming atmosphere.

This is truly a 5/5 star establishment. Great staff, awesome food, delightful atmosphere. It is very roomy, and the greens add to the relaxing environment. There is even outside seating to enjoy the fresh air.

Foods are made fresh and there are so many options (not just what is on the white board). Their ranch and sauces are home made. Plating is fantastic (I like the wooden trays).

Delivery can be obtained via GrubHub or Door dash.

What to take coffee home to prepare on your own? No problem with their JAGS HEAD COFFEE.

I've been to this shop 3 times and everytime I remember I need to come more often! The coffee is so well made and they have lots of flavorful options. I had the passion fruit cheesecake for the first time and it BLEW my mind. Definitely give it a try!

Good spot for a visit, can get a bit busy and noisy but the outdoor seating options are comfortable.

Love the vibe, coffee and food, but the cleanliness is really lacking and is really starting to affect my perception.  Bathrooms were not exactly clean and sitting down and looking at the ground, it looks like no one has swept in a few days.  Some tables are even dirty in the morning.  Hope this gets figured out.  Would hate to see this place affected due to a lack of cleanliness.

I went in on a Saturday around 1030. Their immediate parking lot was full but there's plenty of parking behind the building, so that was no issue.

It was busy and I can understand why. The food menu is really nice for a quick bite and a coffee. I had the Nutella bread and a cappuccino and they were both really excellent. The service was great. They had clearly experienced people behind the counter that were taking orders and serving us up and that was really nice.

There's plenty of room in there, but it does get busy and seats are at a premium that time of morning but that's to be expected and really a testament to the ambience of the restaurant .

I will definitely be returning
Beautiful space! Coffee is good. All of the staff I have met are very rude except for David who is super kind

Such a yummy hazelnut latte and such nice employees. What I love about this place is the atmosphere. I did not feel like I was in Charlotte, and certainly not on that area of South Boulevard. This is my new favorite latte stop!
Great spot with a nice vibe and ambiance !
This place is amazing! Coffee, desserts, and food is great. The place is big so there's always available space. Atmosphere is great too. I really enjoy working from here. Aesthetics are on point.
Great place! Smooth coffee, not bitter. The food looks amazing, need to come back and try it. Friendly staff, and the vibe/space is awesome.
Love their sumaq latte!
Mas o menos  no me gusta mucho

This was my first time here and my experience was nothing short but amazing. I forgot the young gentleman's name at the front but he was so sweet and awesome gave me a great recommendation I got the dulce de leche coffee and it was so good not sweet and not too bitter. It was just right. I didn't get any desserts this time around because I got a sandwich and the ham and cheese bread which was enough filling as it was. Both items were really good and the bread was fantastic. The atmosphere was nice and cozy and welcoming in not dark and dreary. The bathrooms were clean and bright! I wish there were more locations!
Amazing food, drinks, and service but it is a bit pricey

GLUTEN FREE waffles (delicious), GF empanadas (amazing), and GF wraps and protein bowls. A great spot if you are gluten free. Nice vibe. Chairs are wicker which is slightly uncomfortable. But brightly lit windows and nice atmosphere.

I literally walked into Sumaq TODAY and was not in there more than 5 minutes before walking out.  The decor and seating was nice enough but I was very disappointed (after hyping them up based on reviews I'd read to my daughters).  We were not there long enough to be greeted by anyone which was not an issue.  The REAL problem was that there were gnats swarming around the food (lots of them) and noone seemed to be concerned to attempt to cover the food.  Also, I was disappointed to see that the food displayed did not look appealing.  I was VERY disappointed that the carrot cake they are charging $7 plus for looked like a "carrot cake" made in a sheet pant and cut into smaller squares.  They were not layered as advertised on their photos online.  They were literally squares cut from a larger sheet cake.  I am a baker, so I know quality baked goods when I see them and the carrot cake was not it.  There were other baked items where the gnats were that looked burned on the top.  It was very disappointing to see this, as I was so excited about our first (and last trip) to this shop.

In fairness, we were not there long enough to be greeted and the location was very crowded, so sitting was not an option as well. The furniture looked attractive enough in appearance but that was it for the atmosphere. The online photos and videos are much more appealing than what we saw.

I hope this review will ignite some change in this business's standards, as our first visit was very disappointing as compared to the expectations.  Good luck to them, I know running a business is not an easy task but there are some changes needed.

Godspeed Sumaq!

It's nice to have such a nice hidden gem on South Boulevard. Here I can have a business meeting, hang out with friends, grab a quick lunch or just read a book. I would love to see this business expand and share their eclectic vision and flavors in other parts of the City!

Hands down one of the best coffee places in Charlotte. I've been searching for a coffee shop for probably a year now to make a honey lavender oatmeal iced latte and this place nailed it right on the head with the balance of flavor and sweetness. This is my go-to spot now.

I recommend the place, it has several options.
the options with dulce de leche are very delicious.

Sumac is a great cafe with a cozy atmosphere. I went during the winter, but the outdoor patio looks spacious. Everything I tried on the menu was picture perfect and SO delicious! I especially recommend the baked empanadas. If you want some good coffee and chill vibes, this is the place!
I bring dogs here to train them and love the entire experience! So do the dogs

A pretty nice place with decent coffee. I got a cold brew with a shot of mocha. I also got the carrot cake and it was good. The one thing I did not care for was the wooden fork to eat with. A weird texture in the mouth.
Great for work or socialising.
Great coffee and kind service. Very comfortable for a sit-down coffee or date spot
The girl behind the counter was sweet but did not have enough knowledge on the menu items. Food was okay. It's not fancy but worth a visit to get the experience.
Awesome place!  Their Manager, Elmer took great care of our group.

This is a nice quaint place with great coffee.  Met a friend here and we stayed for hours.  We had the Americano and Matcha which were delicious. Customer service was superb. The atmosphere was  perfect!

5 stars all around! I'm in town for work and found this spot- amazing food, AH-MAZING drinks! I had the honey turmeric and a cinnamon oatmilk latte, the greens, a turkey sam, and some killer chocolate cake (I was there for half a day)! LOL. The staff was super friendly too!
Absolutely fantastic coffee and food! Service was great, absolutely recommend.
Perfecto
Tasty coffee and sandwiches. Decor is very cozy with lots of plants.
Cute ambiance, with diverse food offerings. Only like 6 parking spots out front. But so very slow! I ordered a drink TO-GO, and it literally took 30 minutes to receive it. Unacceptable.
Loved this coffee shop so much!

Wow... Peruvians know what they're doing. So far the walpa sandwich, and wrap were incredible. Tres leches out of this world. Coffee is so smooth. Staff is friendly. Clean environment. What more can you ask for? Will be back!

Hip coffee shop with a modern feel to it. I stopped in here the other weekend and ordered a chai, a ham and cheese, and an alfajores. The chai was phenomenal, and I loved the artwork that went into it. Not every coffee shop I go to serves their chai this way so it is always a pleasant surprise when I receive it like this! The ham and cheese reminded me more of a doughy stromboli versus an empanada but I still enjoyed it. This may have just been a miscommunication though since I don't think they meant to say this was an empanada. However, I would love to try their empanadas sometime! Unfortunately, they were just out of them when I had visited. Lastly, that alfajores which was a divine little cookie. The shortbread cookie was perfect and the dulce de leche filling was tasty. They have indoor and outdoor seating and additional parking in the back. It was also getting quite busy after I sat down so it seems to be a popular spot in the area too.
Great place to work on a laptop - the atmosphere here is friendly and upbeat. Brilliant tasting coffee of course, highly recommended!
The barista is on point.  Phenomenal coffee

What a wonderful find. Specialty coffee, delicious treats, and friendly people.

This coffee shop served a great range of fresh roasted coffee. I have been a specialty coffee snob for a while and I was stoked to see a pour over Gesha from El Salvador on the menu!

10/10
Staff is so friendly and the coffee is so well made. Atmosphere is so chill and clean. Lots of seating and some cool seating outdoors. Love this place! We got the Sumaq Latte & Dulce De Leche muffin
Great atmosphere to grab a coffee and chat with friends, plenty of seating!!

Sumaq coffee has a unique, calm, nude color  vibe as soon as you come through the door. With their summer inside tone with the decor. It makes you want to dine in and fellowship with others.  They offer a variety of different coffees, non coffee selection, that pairs well with their food options. I decided to try the Frappe with a Carmel mocha. Yummy! The empanadas were amazing, very moist, and flaky with a side of delicious dipping sauce. They have plenty of space out sitting area inside. Everything was very relaxed and clean.  The staff was helpful with my order.
SO GOOD! Everything is so fresh and so delicious. I loveeeee everything on the menu.

Our first time here and we split a blueberry matcha, Peruvian empanada, and a house chicken wrap. The employees were super friendly, the prices/quality of the food was incredible along with the presentation, and a nice atmosphere inside. The matcha and the food we got was seriously just so good, we will definitely be back to try more of the menu!

We stopped here to get two coffees and a pastry before getting on the road for a long drive. We thought it would take 20 minutes max to grab coffees and get back in the car. The whole thing took almost an hour. There was a crazy line of people that went around the store, unfortunately resulting from the slow cashier and "barista".

When my coffee finally came up, it tasted really off and had nowhere near enough almond milk for a latte. Husband's cold brew was watered down and no cream.

Sumaq seems to be the kind of place that really wants to look like a cute coffee shop with its fake plants, cheap furniture, and store bought pastries, but without the concentration on the quality of product, the facade is obvious.
Absolutely delicious coffee, pastry, and food. 10/10 would recommend

One of the cooler coffee spots in Charlotte. The interior is spacious, warm, and inviting. Plenty of seating, of many varieties both indoor and outdoor.

The food and drink options are unique, especially so the food. Lots of great options for fuller meals, like freshly made sandwiches, wraps, waffles etc. As well as an assortment of delicious pastries.

I got one of the sandwiches and their seasonal pumpkin latte. The latte took about 5 mins to prepare and the food about 15. Both were delicious, the only mention I'd have in regard to being un-positive is that the pumpkin coffee didn't really taste like pumpkin, just more like a seasonal spiced latte. But it was still delicious.

Really recommend this spot, they also have outlets and Wi-Fi it's a great coffee spot to get some work done in if you want to be out :)

Coffee was very good.
Unfortunately the cakes were very old, especially vegan strawberry cake it was many days old.

Maybe we caught them on a bad day, but a 25 minute wait for a double espresso and a latte to go. We almost had to leave before we got our stuff. The latte was good but the espresso had a soapy aftertaste and seemed a little thin. Not what I was hoping for. Overall I was disappointed but I might try again just to see if maybe this was an aberration.
So nice.very dilcious . congratulations

Without being too much of a coffee snob, I haven't found Charlotte to be a great coffee town. But - Sumaq could hold its own anywhere in the country. Comfortable casual, industrial feel inside with the usuals working on their laptops, a creative menu of bakery and freshly made sandwiches, and perfectly made coffee. There's even comfortable outside seatin if you're needing to be chatty or just don't mind some road noise.
Great space with delicious food and authentic coffee! Music and atmosphere brings a relaxing chill vibe and staff is very friendly, always smiling and helpful.
Great place to work! Lattes are good. The quinoa wrap was delicious. Impressed with customer service. Definitely worth checking out!
Great
That pineapple chicken sandwich my brother recommended... just WOW!
I would say it's a bit pricey, but the atmosphere was really great! Great place to meetup with someone for coffee.
Such a gem in an unnoticed neighborhood. Great for hangout, meetings, or work remotely with delicious drinks and treats
First time here and I went crazy with their bread... dulce de leche and Guava. I loved everything. I will be back

Sumaq is a beautiful cafe with good service. I purchased 3 cinnamon rolls. They were hard, dry and tough to chew. We couldn't eat them.
Very disappointing for such a lovely place.
However, we also purchased a Nutella roll that my daughter said was amazing!
Maybe just a bad day for cinnamon rolls there?
This place is a vibe for sure. There are charging outlets at every seat and enough seating space for everyone inside and out. The food guys.. it's delicious. Try the wraps and empanadas
Don't take kids here. They will tell you to be quite. Please set a age limit if you don't want kids to come.

This is one of my favorite coffee and food spots in the area. Expect South American flavors, specifically if Peruvian origin, in the food, drink, and atmosphere. You can come for breakfast to have a pastry or empanada with your coffee. For lunch or dinner, I strongly suggest the Wasi House sandwich. It is shredded chicken, bacon, caramelized pineapples, cheese and pepper sauce. If the person preparing it toasts the middle of the sandwich at the cut, the crispness adds another layer of texture and flavor. This time someone did not do it, but the sandwich is still one of the only ones I fawn over in Charlotte.

Now that Sumaq latte is a whole vibe. You can get a cinnamon latte almost anywhere, but I promise you that this one tastes like REAL cinnamon and not a flavored syrupy mess. It is the perfect balance of sweet, spicy, and bitter. I was suggested this the first time I came and can't move myself to try anything else. If they have chica morada, Peruvian purple corn drink, do order it. I like to order it with no ice to take home where I add tequila or dark rum. It is perfectly fine as is, but this cocktail takes greatness to perfection for me.

The interior? See the video I posted. The outdoor area transports you to Peru though you are perched directly on South Blvd. If you can tune out the traffic, you can enter bliss.

Big thumbs up to the stools that a disabled plus size vertically challenged woman to sit with ease. This is a rarity at establishments.
Great coffee and pastries
Very good and strong coffee.  Make sure you describe how you want your drink well as there's no cream or sugar out for you to set up as you like.  Food is good
INCREDIBLE!!!  Wish we had one close to home in Denver!

Super chevere todo,los chicos de la barra lo mejor y el ambiente ni se diga, mi lugar favorito para compartir con amigas o simplemente pasar el rato 
Volvere todas las veces que pueda!!
Nunca responden el telefono para hacer ordenes si no sirve o si no responden no pongan numero de telefono para llamar y ordenar !!!!!!!!!!
Me encanto y lo recomiendo 100%  si quieres un buen cafe este es el lugar correcto
Great environment. Great staff. Great food.
Estupendo lugar para compartir

Love this place!! Went on a Sunday morning and it was quiet and Staff are sweet and vibe is so comfortable and cozy. Great place for working with plenty of outlets and wifi available. Clean and food was delicious   coffee was clutch and I highly recommend this spot!
Cute spot with tasty food! I tried the dulce de leche latte, lemon cake, & chicken empanada.

One of my favorite coffee shops in Charlotte. Not because it's necessarily the best coffee, but because it's something you won't find anywhere else. I love the Sumaq latte (house cinnamon syrup), waffle with guava and the empanadas! I've never had a waffle with cheese in the middle and the guava jam tops off the sweet and savory combo. The empanadas are delicious and the sauce that it comes with is perfect. I've had empanadas all over Charlotte, but these are the best! My favorite are the Peruvian!
Needed a place to work for a few hours and this place was perfect. Lots of seating, friendly atmosphere, great lighting and not too mention my Lulun Gratin and Latte were SO good.

Sumaq Coffee was a quick pit stop for us to get coffee, and it didn't disappoint. We got the Sumaq Coffee and it tasted just perfect. The service was polite and quick. They sell sandwiches and pastries as well, which I'm looking forward to try the next time I'm here.

The indoor seating area was pretty busy on the afternoon we visited, which told us it's a good cafe to chill. The parking area outside is pretty small. Overall a decent cafe to get coffee.
Really nice and chill coffee spot. Unique food items like sandwiches and desserts with a South American influence. It has nice seating inside and out and good coffee!
This place is great! The atmosphere is wonderful and the employees are great. Had a special request for a drink and they went out of their way to be sure I liked it

Stopped in to have lunch with a friend and was so pleased with this spot. The staff were super friendly and the food was amazing. I had the panka pesto sandwich, the alfajores, and a cold brew, all of which were perfectly made. Most definitely will be back!
Delicious coffee and food!
Lovely coffee place, calm, cool interior, great coffee and cake.
Empanadas are excellent. Coffee is great mocachino iced is the ticket
I've been looking for a great coffee shop for a while and I guess I finally found it the Cortado is really good
Kind staff and great products.
Had the Wasi sandwich - awesome 5 stars!!!!!!
Okay coffee but not very good food options for snacking

First visit. Bright, spacious shop and very clean. Bathrooms were immaculate.

Lots of rich pastry options. I am not a fan of the roaster they carry. The cold brew option was not in stock so I had their nitro cold brew. It was a lighter roast and had good flavor. One complaint: the nitro was served on ice.

Prices seemed slightly over par. Service was acceptable. With all the coffee options in CLT and SouthEnd, I will likely not return.
Great food, great place to have good coffee and desserts

The Wasi house sandwich is absolutely incredible. The sumaq latte was also fantastic! Highly recommend. Also there is a tree inside the establishment and it really sets the vibe of the shop. Great place to hangout and catch up with friends, or even work remotely.

Lovely coffee shop!
Great atmosphere - even my non coffee drinking boyfriend loved the raspberry lemonade!

#sumaq #coffee #bakery #good
They have a delicious decaf. You can't even tell the difference. The service is always nice and friendly. They have delicious food too. Especially the empanadas.
Beautiful coffee shop, great staff, amazing coffee.
Cool cheesecake and a hot chocolate!
Delicious craft coffee, friendly service, and an inviting, west coast type atmosphere. Bright and airy, plenty of places to sit and work or socialize.
Atmosphere is bright, clean and social. Great place to have a convo or put your head down and work.

#1 COFFEE IN CHARLOTTE
Incredible quality coffee (must try Sumaq syrup) amazing food and fiiire deserts. (Passion Fruit Cheesecake??)

They have live music every now and then and love to support / connect with the community. If you're passing by 704 or a local you def need to come by south blvd and see for yourself!
It's such a cute coffee shop. My latte was delicious! I definitely would recommend trying them out!
